$ Excel Object Model: PivotField
@ PivotField

{ Some interesting properties

  Some interesting properties of the `pivotField` object include, imho:
    • `dataRange` is the → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Range[`range`] that the data that is represented by a pivot field occupies on a → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Worksheet[worksheet].
    • `labelRange` is also a `range`, but it unclear to me what it represents.
    • `dataType` which is assigned one of the values of the → https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/office/vba/api/excel.xlpivotfielddatatype[`xlPivotFieldDataType`] enumeration: `xlNumber`, `xlText` or `xlDate`.
    • `position`
    • `showingInAxis`
    • `childField`
    • `function`
    • `groupLevel`
    • `name`
    • `caption`
    • `numberFormat`
    • `orientation` which is assigned a member of the → https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/office/vba/api/excel.xlpivotfieldorientation[`xlPivotFieldOrientatinon`] enumeration: `xlColumnField`, `xlDataField`, `xlHidden`, `xlPageField`, `xlRowField`
    • `showAllItems`: a → development/languages/VBA/language/datatypes/boolean
    • `memoryUsed`
    • `autoSortOrder`: one of the → https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/office/vba/api/excel.xlsortorder[`xlSortOrder`] members, `xlAscending`, `xlDescending`, `xlManual`
    • `autoSortField`

}

sa:

  → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/PivotTable[`pivotTable`]

  → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model
